{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":858,"text":"Vincent Moon: How can we use computers,"},{"time":4677,"text":"cameras, microphones to represent the world"},{"time":9172,"text":"in an alternative way,"},{"time":11336,"text":"as much as possible?"},{"time":13370,"text":"How, maybe, is it possible to use the Internet"},{"time":16324,"text":"to create a new form of cinema?"},{"time":20042,"text":"And actually, why do we record?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25035,"text":"Well, it is with such simple questions in mind"},{"time":27953,"text":"that I started to make films 10 years ago,"},{"time":31936,"text":"first with a friend, Christophe Abric."},{"time":35424,"text":"He had a website, La Blogothèque,"},{"time":37809,"text":"dedicated to independent music."},{"time":40475,"text":"We were crazy about music."},{"time":42130,"text":"We wanted to represent \nmusic in a different way,"},{"time":44822,"text":"to film the music we love,\nthe musicians we admired,"},{"time":47410,"text":"as much as possible, far \nfrom the music industry"},{"time":50871,"text":"and far from the cliches attached to it."},{"time":53253,"text":"We started to publish every week"},{"time":56219,"text":"sessions on the Internet."},{"time":57969,"text":"We are going to see a few extracts now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65944,"text":"From Grizzly Bear in the shower"},{"time":69744,"text":"to Sigur Ros playing in a Parisian cafe."},{"time":76570,"text":"From Phoenix playing by the Eiffel Tower"},{"time":81358,"text":"to Tom Jones in his \nhotel room in New York."},{"time":86241,"text":"From Arcade Fire in an elevator"},{"time":88707,"text":"in the Olympia"},{"time":90856,"text":"to Beirut going down\na staircase in Brooklyn."},{"time":96486,"text":"From R.E.M. in a car"},{"time":100500,"text":"to The National around a table at night"},{"time":102863,"text":"in the south of France."},{"time":106620,"text":"From Bon Iver playing with some friends"},{"time":109952,"text":"in an apartment in Montmartre"},{"time":112925,"text":"to Yeasayer having a long night,"},{"time":116783,"text":"and many, many, many more"},{"time":119866,"text":"unknown or very famous bands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122370,"text":"We published all those films"},{"time":123926,"text":"for free on the Internet,"},{"time":125882,"text":"and we wanted to share"},{"time":128898,"text":"all those films and represent music"},{"time":131068,"text":"in a different way."},{"time":133828,"text":"We wanted to create \nanother type of intimacy"},{"time":136998,"text":"using all those new technologies."},{"time":138662,"text":"At the time, 10 years ago actually,"},{"time":141768,"text":"there was no such project on the Internet,"},{"time":144018,"text":"and I guess that's why the project we \nwere making, the Take Away Shows,"},{"time":147663,"text":"got quite successful,"},{"time":148940,"text":"reaching millions of viewers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152720,"text":"After a while, I got a bit —"},{"time":155920,"text":"I wanted to go somewhere else."},{"time":157830,"text":"I felt the need to travel and\nto discover some other music,"},{"time":160800,"text":"to explore the world,"},{"time":162735,"text":"going to other corners,"},{"time":164523,"text":"and actually it was also"},{"time":166564,"text":"this idea of nomadic cinema,\nsort of, that I had in mind."},{"time":170535,"text":"How could the use of new technologies \nand the road fit together?"},{"time":177583,"text":"How could I edit my films in a bus"},{"time":179431,"text":"crossing the Andes?"},{"time":181466,"text":"So I went on five-year travels"},{"time":183400,"text":"around the globe."},{"time":185334,"text":"I started at the time in the digital film \nand music label collection Petites Planètes,"},{"time":190310,"text":"which was also an homage to\nFrench filmmaker Chris Marker."},{"time":193526,"text":"We're going to see now a few more extracts"},{"time":196371,"text":"of those new films."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203356,"text":"From the tecno brega diva of\nnorthern Brazil, Gaby Amarantos"},{"time":212904,"text":"to a female ensemble in Chechnya."},{"time":219241,"text":"From experimental electronic music \nin Singapore with One Man Nation"},{"time":226368,"text":"to Brazilian icon Tom Zé singing\non his rooftop in São Paolo."},{"time":234672,"text":"From The Bambir, the great \nrock band from Armenia"},{"time":239846,"text":"to some traditional songs"},{"time":242303,"text":"in a restaurant in Tbilisi, Georgia."},{"time":247731,"text":"From White Shoes, a great retro \npop band from Jakarta, Indonesia"},{"time":255012,"text":"to DakhaBrakha, the revolutionary \nband from Kiev, Ukraine."},{"time":262320,"text":"From Tomi Lebrero"},{"time":264020,"text":"and his bandoneon and his friends\nin Buenos Aires, Argentina,"},{"time":268136,"text":"to many other places"},{"time":270735,"text":"and musicians around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273412,"text":"My desire was to make it as a trek."},{"time":276381,"text":"To do all those films,"},{"time":278147,"text":"it would have been impossible"},{"time":279778,"text":"with a big company behind me,"},{"time":281229,"text":"with a structure or anything."},{"time":282630,"text":"I was traveling alone with a backpack —"},{"time":285711,"text":"computer, camera, microphones in it."},{"time":288180,"text":"Alone, actually, but \njust with local people,"},{"time":290965,"text":"meeting my team, which was absolutely not"},{"time":293800,"text":"professional people, on the spot there,"},{"time":297715,"text":"going from one place to another"},{"time":299976,"text":"and to make cinema as a trek."},{"time":301457,"text":"I really believed that cinema could be"},{"time":304352,"text":"this very simple thing:"},{"time":306544,"text":"I want to make a film and you're going \nto give me a place to stay for the night."},{"time":311263,"text":"I give you a moment of cinema\nand you offer me a capirinha."},{"time":316195,"text":"Well, or other drinks,"},{"time":318480,"text":"depending on where you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320715,"text":"In Peru, they drink pisco sour."},{"time":324172,"text":"Well, when I arrived in Peru, actually,"},{"time":329014,"text":"I had no idea about what I would do there."},{"time":334289,"text":"And I just had one phone number, actually,"},{"time":341569,"text":"of one person."},{"time":343064,"text":"Three months later,"},{"time":344407,"text":"after traveling all around the \ncountry, I had recorded 33 films,"},{"time":348735,"text":"only with the help of local people,"},{"time":351755,"text":"only with the help of people"},{"time":354217,"text":"that I was asking all the \ntime the same question:"},{"time":356469,"text":"What is important to record here today?"},{"time":361515,"text":"By living in such a way,"},{"time":363343,"text":"by working without any structure,"},{"time":366174,"text":"I was able to react to the moment"},{"time":371369,"text":"and to decide, oh, this is \nimportant to make now."},{"time":374787,"text":"This is important to \nrecord that whole person."},{"time":377033,"text":"This is important to create this exchange."},{"time":381049,"text":"When I went to Chechnya,"},{"time":384100,"text":"the first person I met"},{"time":386310,"text":"looked at me and was like,"},{"time":388520,"text":"\"What are you doing here?"},{"time":390730,"text":"Are you a journalist? NGO? Politics?"},{"time":393734,"text":"What kind of problems \nare you going to study?\""},{"time":396872,"text":"Well, I was there to research"},{"time":399482,"text":"on Sufi rituals in Chechnya, actually —"},{"time":402440,"text":"incredible culture of Sufism in Chechnya,"},{"time":405575,"text":"which is absolutely unknown \noutside of the region."},{"time":410849,"text":"As soon as people understood"},{"time":412903,"text":"that I would give them those films —"},{"time":415343,"text":"I would publish them online for free\nunder a Creative Commons license,"},{"time":417953,"text":"but I would also really \ngive them to the people"},{"time":419955,"text":"and I would let them do \nwhat they want with it."},{"time":421767,"text":"I just want to represent \nthem in a beautiful light."},{"time":423690,"text":"I just want to portray them in a way that"},{"time":426378,"text":"their grandchildren are going\nto look at their grandfather,"},{"time":429649,"text":"and they're going to be like,"},{"time":431204,"text":"\"Whoa, my grandfather is as \ncool as Beyoncé.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":436288,"text":"It's a really important thing."},{"time":438144,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441643,"text":"It's really important,"},{"time":442948,"text":"because that's the way"},{"time":444604,"text":"people are going to look differently at \ntheir own culture, at their own land."},{"time":448430,"text":"They're going to think about it differently."},{"time":450614,"text":"It may be a way to maintain \na certain diversity."},{"time":457256,"text":"Why you will record?"},{"time":460549,"text":"Hmm. There's a really good quote"},{"time":462710,"text":"by American thinker Hakim Bey"},{"time":464634,"text":"which says, \"Every recording"},{"time":468060,"text":"is a tombstone of a live performance.\""},{"time":471966,"text":"It's a really good \nsentence to keep in mind"},{"time":474981,"text":"nowadays in an era saturated by images."},{"time":478889,"text":"What's the point of that?"},{"time":480409,"text":"Where do we go with it?"},{"time":483189,"text":"I was researching. I was still \nkeeping this idea in mind:"},{"time":486470,"text":"What's the point?"},{"time":489085,"text":"I was researching on music, trying to pull,"},{"time":491305,"text":"trying to get closer to a certain origin of it."},{"time":494173,"text":"Where is this all coming from?"},{"time":496367,"text":"I am French. I had no idea about"},{"time":498718,"text":"what I would discover, \nwhich is a very simple thing:"},{"time":501164,"text":"Everything was sacred, at first,"},{"time":503949,"text":"and music was spiritual healing."},{"time":509472,"text":"How could I use my camera,"},{"time":512767,"text":"my little tool, to get closer"},{"time":517255,"text":"and maybe not only capture the trance"},{"time":519701,"text":"but find an equivalent, \na cine-trance, maybe,"},{"time":525595,"text":"something in complete harmony"},{"time":528047,"text":"with the people?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530815,"text":"That is now my new research I'm doing"},{"time":535154,"text":"on spirituality, on new \nspirits around the world."},{"time":539575,"text":"Maybe a few more extracts now."},{"time":547913,"text":"From the Tana Toraja \nfuneral ritual in Indonesia"},{"time":557127,"text":"to an Easter ceremony \nin the north of Ethiopia."},{"time":563629,"text":"From jathilan, a popular trance ritual"},{"time":566198,"text":"on the island of Java,"},{"time":570270,"text":"to Umbanda in the north of Brazil."},{"time":578580,"text":"The Sufi rituals of Chechnya"},{"time":585386,"text":"to a mass in the holiest \nchurch of Armenia."},{"time":594846,"text":"Some Sufi songs in Harar,"},{"time":596691,"text":"the holy city of Ethiopia,"},{"time":602102,"text":"to an ayahuasca ceremony"},{"time":604281,"text":"deep in the Amazon of \nPeru with the Shipibo."},{"time":611996,"text":"Then to my new project, \nthe one I'm doing now"},{"time":614162,"text":"here in Brazil, named \"Híbridos.\""},{"time":615798,"text":"I'm doing it with Priscilla Telmon."},{"time":617584,"text":"It's research on the new \nspiritualities all around the country."},{"time":622547,"text":"This is my quest, my own little quest \nof what I call experimental ethnography,"},{"time":628505,"text":"trying to hybrid all \nthose different genres,"},{"time":636773,"text":"trying to regain a certain complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641485,"text":"Why do we record?"},{"time":644000,"text":"I was still there."},{"time":646681,"text":"I really believe cinema teaches us to see."},{"time":650494,"text":"The way we show the world"},{"time":651900,"text":"is going to change the \nway we see this world,"},{"time":656150,"text":"and we live in a moment where the mass media"},{"time":658290,"text":"are doing a terrible, terrible job"},{"time":660899,"text":"at representing the world:"},{"time":663126,"text":"violence, extremists,"},{"time":667160,"text":"only spectacular events,"},{"time":669314,"text":"only simplifications of everyday life."},{"time":671541,"text":"I think we are recording"},{"time":673666,"text":"to regain a certain complexity."},{"time":677252,"text":"To reinvent life today,"},{"time":682423,"text":"we have to make new forms of images."},{"time":686213,"text":"And it's very simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688377,"text":"Muito obrigado."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691060,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702204,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Vincent, Vincent, Vincent."},{"time":705263,"text":"Merci. We have to prepare for\nthe following performance,"},{"time":708301,"text":"and I have a question for you,\nand the question is this:"},{"time":710888,"text":"You show up in places like the \nones you just have shown us,"},{"time":714914,"text":"and you are carrying a camera"},{"time":716818,"text":"and I assume that you are welcome"},{"time":719313,"text":"but you are not always absolutely welcome."},{"time":722000,"text":"You walk into sacred rituals,"},{"time":724634,"text":"private moments in a village, a town,"},{"time":728471,"text":"a group of people."},{"time":730680,"text":"How do you break the barrier"},{"time":732576,"text":"when you show up with a lens?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"VM: I think you break it with your body,"},{"time":740605,"text":"more than with your knowledge."},{"time":743243,"text":"That's what it taught me to travel,"},{"time":745610,"text":"to trust the memory of the body"},{"time":748433,"text":"more than the memory of the brain."},{"time":751083,"text":"The respect is stepping forward,"},{"time":753395,"text":"not stepping backward, and I really think that"},{"time":756240,"text":"by engaging your body in the\nmoment, in the ceremony,"},{"time":759190,"text":"in the places, people welcome you"},{"time":761553,"text":"and understand your energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763237,"text":"BG: You told me that most of the videos"},{"time":764900,"text":"you have made are \nactually one single shot."},{"time":767569,"text":"You don't do much editing."},{"time":769177,"text":"I mean, you edited the ones for us"},{"time":770921,"text":"at the beginning of the sessions\nbecause of the length, etc."},{"time":773486,"text":"Otherwise, you just go in and capture"},{"time":775313,"text":"whatever happens in front of your eyes"},{"time":777119,"text":"without much planning, and so is that the case?"},{"time":779853,"text":"It's correct?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781586,"text":"VM: My idea is that I think that"},{"time":783594,"text":"as long as we don't cut, in a way,"},{"time":787614,"text":"as long as we let the viewer watch,"},{"time":790719,"text":"more and more viewers \nare going to feel closer,"},{"time":793688,"text":"are going to get closer to the moment,"},{"time":796501,"text":"to that moment and to that place."},{"time":800337,"text":"I really think of that as a matter \nof respecting the viewer,"},{"time":803869,"text":"to not cut all the time from one place to another,"},{"time":807581,"text":"to just let the time go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809645,"text":"BG: Tell me in a few words \nabout your new project,"},{"time":811749,"text":"\"Híbridos,\" here in Brazil."},{"time":813284,"text":"Just before coming to \nTEDGlobal, you have actually"},{"time":815062,"text":"been traveling around \nthe country for that."},{"time":817333,"text":"Tell us a couple of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819156,"text":"VM: \"Híbridos\" is — \nI really believe Brazil,"},{"time":821485,"text":"far from the cliches, is the greatest\nreligious country in the world,"},{"time":825658,"text":"the greatest country \nin terms of spirituality"},{"time":828504,"text":"and in experimentations in spiritualities."},{"time":831541,"text":"And it's a big project I'm \ndoing over this year,"},{"time":834515,"text":"which is researching in very\ndifferent regions of Brazil,"},{"time":839315,"text":"in very different forms of cults,"},{"time":841420,"text":"and trying to understand \nhow people live together"},{"time":843308,"text":"with spirituality nowadays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844753,"text":"BG: The man who is going to \nappear onstage momentarily,"},{"time":848489,"text":"and Vincent's going to introduce him,"},{"time":850199,"text":"is one of the subjects of \none of his past videos."},{"time":853851,"text":"When did you do a video with him?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855718,"text":"VM: I guess four years ago,"},{"time":858272,"text":"four years in my first travel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860758,"text":"BG: So it was one of \nyour first ones in Brazil."},{"time":863602,"text":"VM: It was amongst the \nfirst ones in Brazil, yeah."},{"time":865833,"text":"I shot the film in Recife,"},{"time":867290,"text":"in the place where he is from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869259,"text":"BG: So let's introduce him. \nWho are we waiting for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":872269,"text":"VM: I'll just make it very short."},{"time":873740,"text":"It's a very great honor for \nme to welcome onstage"},{"time":876343,"text":"one of the greatest Brazilian \nmusicians of all time."},{"time":879304,"text":"Please welcome Naná Vasconcelos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881643,"text":"BG: Naná Vasconcelos!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":883555,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":890563,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1147657,"text":"Naná Vasconcelos: Let's go to the jungle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1427636,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}